{"id":484,"date":"2007-03-15T12:50:12","date_gmt":"2007-03-15T17:50:12","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/love_at_first_glancia.php"},"modified":"2007-03-15T12:50:12","modified_gmt":"2007-03-15T17:50:12","slug":"love_at_first_glancia","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/love_at_first_glancia.php","title":{"rendered":"Love at First Glancia"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/lancia_logo.gif\" alt=\"Lancia, Before and After\" \/><\/p>\n<p>For some reason &mdash; contrary to my usual disdain for shadows and gradients &mdash; when it comes to car logos I like mine shiny and bevely. As If yanked from the hood of the car and glued to a business card. Italian automobile manufacturer, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.lancia.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Lancia<\/a>, celebrating its 100 years of car-making, has just <a href=\"http:\/\/www.designweek.co.uk\/Articles\/134243\/New+identity+for+Lancia.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">launched<\/a> a new identity designed by Italian design firm <a href=http:\/\/www.robilantassociati.com\/\" target=\"_blank\">Robilanti Associati<\/a>. While retaining the original and, I assume, recognizable shape, Lancia was able to add a hefty dose of attitude to the new badge, and they are not hesitant to play it up; from their web site: &#8220;&hellip; the shield has more depth, the 4 spokes have become 2 aggressive points&hellip;.&#8221; <em>Aggressive<\/em> is rarely a word used to publicly describe any corporation. This new logo exudes <em>car-ness<\/em> and luxury, via a nice condensed serif (with a mean LA ligature) and is well positioned to support the new tag line, &#8220;The Evolution of 100 Years of Elegance and Attitude.&#8221; Now, <em>that&#8217;s<\/em> how I like my car logos.<\/p>\n<p>Thanks to <a href=\"http:\/\/www.namedevelopment.com\/blog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Jon Fredkove<\/a> for the tip. Large image of the logo after the jump.<\/p><!--more--><p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/lancia_logo_large.png\" alt=\"Lancia New Logo\" \/><\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/images\/excerpt_empty.gif\" alt=\"Excerpt Empty\" \/>","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"episode_type":"","audio_file":"","duration":"","filesize":"","date_recorded":"","explicit":"","block":"","filesize_raw":""},"categories":[59,9,26],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/484"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=484"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/484\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=484"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=484"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=484"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}